# Billing and cache

## Billing (Turso)

- Schema lives in `schema.go`; migrate via `store.Migrate`
- Budget model: `limit_microusd`, `spent_microusd`, `reserved_microusd`
- Reserve before forward; settle actual; release unused reservation
- API keys: store `key_hash` + `key_prefix` only
- Usage statuses: `allowed`, `blocked_budget`, `blocked_loop`, `provider_error`, `completed`

## Cache (Upstash)

- REST client only (no Redis TCP protocol assumption)
- Circuit breaker: INCR + EXPIRE on session+payload hash; trip at `TOKENGUARD_LOOP_THRESHOLD`
- Guarded mode must fail closed if Redis ping/ops fail

Keep micro-USD math integer-only. Schema changes need matching store methods and tests.
